{"name": "fastapi-vite", "metadata": {"name": "fastapi-vite", "version": "0.3.2", "classifiers": ["Framework :: AsyncIO", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/cofin/fastapi-vite", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["fastapi", "Jinja2", "typer"], "summary": "Integration utilities for FastAPI and ViteJS.", "upload_time": 1640975279}, "documentation": ["# fastapi-vite\n\nIntegration for FastAPI and Vite JS\n\n## what?\n\nThis package is designed to make working with javascript assets easier.\n\nfastapi-vite enables the jinja filters required to render asset URLs to jinja templates\n\nInspired by `django-vite` @ [https://github.com/MrBin99/django-vite]\n\n## installation\n\nInstall using pip\n\n```shell\npip install fastapi-vite\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nConfigure Jinja templating for FastAPI\n\n```python\nimport fastapi_vite\n\ntemplates = Jinja2Templates(directory='templates')\ntemplates.env.globals['vite_hmr_client'] = fastapi_vite.vite_hmr_client\ntemplates.env.globals['vite_asset'] = fastapi_vite.vite_asset\n\n```\n\n### Configure Vite\n\nHere is an example used to test this plugin\n\n```javascript\nimport { defineConfig } from 'vite'\nimport reactRefresh from '@vitejs/plugin-react-refresh'\nconst Dotenv = require(\"dotenv\");\nimport path from \"path\";\nDotenv.config({ path: path.join(__dirname, \".env\") });\n\nconst STATIC_URL = process.env.STATIC_URL;\n// https://vitejs.dev/config/\nexport default defineConfig({\n  base: `${STATIC_URL}`,\n  clearScreen: false,\n  plugins: [\n    reactRefresh(),\n\n  ],\n  build: {\n    target: \"esnext\",\n    outDir: \"./static/\",\n    emptyOutDir: true,\n    assetsDir: \"\",\n    manifest: true,\n    rollupOptions: {\n      input:  \"./assets/javascript/main.tsx\"\n    },\n  },\n\n  root: \".\", // You can change the root path as you wish\n\n})\n\n```\n\n### Configure Static Assets\n\n### Configure Templates\n\n\\*render_vite_hmr no-op when in production.\n\n```html\n{{ render_vite_hmr_client() }}\n\n<script\n  type=\"text/javascript\"\n  defer\n  src=\"{{ asset_url('javascript/main.tsx') }}\"\n></script>\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "fastapi_vite", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "fastapi_vite.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "fastapi_vite.settings", "xref": {"fqname": "fastapi_vite.config.settings", "project": null}}, {"name": "fastapi_vite.vite_asset", "xref": {"fqname": "fastapi_vite.loader.vite_asset", "project": null}}, {"name": "fastapi_vite.vite_asset_url", "xref": {"fqname": "fastapi_vite.loader.vite_asset_url", "project": null}}, {"name": "fastapi_vite.vite_hmr_client", "xref": {"fqname": "fastapi_vite.loader.vite_hmr_client", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "fastapi_vite.loader", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "fastapi_vite.loader.vite_hmr_client", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "Markup", "xref": {"fqname": "jinja2.Markup", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Generates the script tag for the Vite WS client for HMR.\nOnly used in development, in production this method returns\nan empty string.\n\nIf react is enabled,\nReturns:\n    str -- The script tag or an empty string."]}, {"name": "fastapi_vite.loader.vite_asset", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "scripts_attrs", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Dict", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "Markup", "xref": {"fqname": "jinja2.Markup", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Generates all assets include tags for the file in argument.\nGenerates all scripts tags for this file and all its dependencies\n(JS and CSS) by reading the manifest file (for production only).\nIn development Vite imports all dependencies by itself.\nPlace this tag in <head> section of yout page\n(this function marks automaticaly <script> as \"async\" and \"defer\").\n\nArguments:\n    path {str} -- Path to a Vite asset to include.\n\nKeyword Arguments:\n    scripts_attrs {Optional[Dict[str, str]]} -- Override attributes added to scripts tags. (default: {None})\n    with_imports {bool} -- If generate assets for dependant assets of this one. (default: {True})\n\nReturns:\n    str -- All tags to import this asset in yout HTML page."]}, {"name": "fastapi_vite.loader.vite_asset_url", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Generates only the URL of an asset managed by ViteJS.\nWarning, this function does not generate URLs for dependant assets.\n\nArguments:\n    path {str} -- Path to a Vite asset.\n\nReturns:\n    [type] -- The URL of this asset."]}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "fastapi_vite.loader.ViteLoader", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "fastapi_vite.loader.ViteLoader.__new__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Singleton manifest loader"]}, {"name": "fastapi_vite.loader.ViteLoader.parse_manifest", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"nam